data.title: Inside Bryce Dallas Howard's Glamorous L.A. Home
data.meta_description: Today AD is welcomed to Los Angeles by actor/director Bryce Dallas Howard and husband Seth Gabel for a tour of their new home, an "organically glamorous" space paying homage to classic Hollywood with an undercurrent of California vibes. To realize her vision, Bryce recruited family friend Claire Thomas to mastermind the decoration of the four-bedroom, two-story new-build. “We immediately knew that the core color palette for the house was going to be pink and green,” Thomas says. “I always joke that I only use redhead colors—that is, colors that redheads look great in. I’m a redhead and Bryce is a redhead so it works.” Shop Bryce and Seth’s home style!Honor nature the Bryce and Seth way—with lots of interesting floral arrangements and house plants:(Similar) Pampas Grass Bouquet: https://fave.co/3aKde20(Similar) Fernwood Mikado Snake Plant: https://fave.co/3zi2Okr(Similar) Unplanted Gromeo Vertical Planter: https://fave.co/3MpuhTW(Similar) Silk Cherry Blossom Stem: https://fave.co/3GYt996(Similar) Real Touch Poppy White Navy Center: https://fave.co/3GTaB9WLove the couple’s wallpaper moments? It’s easy to create your own accent walls with the help of some vibrant finds:House of Hackney Dinosauria Wallpaper: https://fave.co/3xkASd2(Similar) Dark Woodland Wallpaper: https://fave.co/3NFMzCd(Similar) Jackalope Wallpaper: https://fave.co/3zlcz12(Similar) Red Tulip Wallpaper: https://fave.co/3tmpBYr(Similar) Orange Retro Floral Removable Wallpaper: https://fave.co/3GTJhIG(Similar) Pink Orange Retro Floral Removable Wallpaper: https://fave.co/3NCpRukBryce’s home includes lots of easy-to-shop pieces, including exact furniture from Lulu & Georgia, Anthropologie, Outer, and more:Serena & Lily Shore Dining Chair: https://fave.co/3x9NQdALulu and Georgia Jody Sectional Sofa: https://fave.co/3xpr1nEAnthropologie Kalle Sculptural Oak Console: https://fave.co/3mk6H0tAnthropologie Rhys Leather Bed: https://fave.co/3mi4ZNhOuter Brown Wicker Outdoor Armchair: https://fave.co/3Ns1qQl(Similar) Round Terrazzo Table Top: https://fave.co/3teViCPWe love the couples' playful pink-and-green aesthetic. Create your own dual color scheme with a few of these bright accents to start:SMEG 50's Retro Style Aesthetic Drip Filter Coffee Machine: https://amzn.to/3GWB7iTSMEG Retro Line Pastel Green Slot Toaster: https://amzn.to/3Mq1tuJGreat Jones Dutch Baby: https://fave.co/3MqbqrUTrudon Josephine scented candle: https://fave.co/3tdGtAH(Similar) Balta Mod-Tod Tigre Kids Tiger Area Rug: https://fave.co/3Mtx3rj(Similar) Armadillo Agra Rug: https://fave.co/3thaOOAWhen you buy something through our retail links, we earn an affiliate commission.
data.text:
Hey AD.

Hello, hello, hello.

Welcome to California.

My name is Bryce Dallas Howard, and this is my house.

Come on, check it out.

[upbeat music]

So when folks come by to visit,

usually the first thing they notice

and ask about are the pet portraits.

They're by Michael Harnish.

I love these because I love my pets.

I'm actually directing a documentary right now

for Disney+ called Pets.

All of the light fixtures in the home are by Lightology.

I love this light fixture.

It just reminds me of the ocean.

The console is by Anthropologie,

and there's a beautiful vintage piece here.

The next room I'm excited to show you is right through here.

[light music]

This office, we could call our office,

but the truth is is that it's Seth's office.

We share though.

She's in here a lot.

[Bryce laughs]

Yeah, yeah I am.

I creep in here all the time 'cause I love it.

So the inspiration for me

initially came from Star Trek: The Next Generation,

but we were kind of going for a retro futurism,

like a 1980s depiction of what the future would look like.

Kind of an amalgamation of Bow house and art deco

and neo futuristic vibes,

and I feel like Claire Thomas, who we're working with,

helped make that here,

and I think it's absolutely incredible.

So with the window treatments,

I had done a Picasso series and fell in love with cubism,

and as you'll see throughout the house,

we have a lot of nods to different jobs that we've done

and work that we love,

and so we put the Picasso vibes in here.

So this is one of my favorite things in the house

that Bryce finally allowed me to get.

I've been craving a neon clock for a very long time.

I've loved neon clocks and this is from the 1930s,

from Germany, and it does this awesome thing.

Go for it.

I mean, how cool is that?

We love nature, we love plants, we love green,

and so making sure that we had a lot of plants in the home

was very important to us.

So the inspiration was late Cretaceous period,

so hence this bad boy over here.

[Seth] Yeah, prehistoric vibes to the plant life.

[Bryce] Everywhere, yeah.

[Seth] Yeah.

[light music]

So this is the dining room

and we were really inspired by a few things,

but specifically Miyazaki, the filmmaker Miyazaki.

We really wanted this room to feel like nature

and to feel like a forest and to feel like starry night

and clouds, to just really feel like we were outside.

We have incredible wallpaper, it's by Schumacher,

and it makes me feel like I'm in a magical forest in Japan.

The rug is from Armadillo and Co, and I love their ethos.

They're a pro-social company

and that's very, very, very important to me,

especially in a room like this

where we're trying to honor the planet.

Our ceilings are actually an antique brass

and it's really beautiful because it reflects the light.

Again, a fixture by Lightology,

and this kind of just reminded us of stars

because it reflected the ceiling.

It's just kind of scrumptious.

[light music]

So Claire Thomas and I love a loud powder room.

Instead of kind of ripping out all this tile and whatnot,

we decided to work with it,

and so here's some beautiful wallpaper

that has special meaning for my husband and I.

We met in the early aughts,

and when we had just been dating for a couple of months,

I went to go do a theater program in Amsterdam.

One of the things that Amsterdam is known for

is their beautiful tulip fields.

Sort of in an homage to the beginning of our relationship,

we decided to have sort of a tulip theme

throughout the house.

So that's the story of the loud powder room.

[upbeat music]

So this piece is from Tap In

and we have quite a number of pieces actually

from Tap In Collective.

And something that was really exciting about Tap In

is that they support living artists, emerging artists,

and it allows someone like myself

who has zero courage

when it comes to becoming an art collector

to actually start to have a collection of our own.

[light music]

Hey you.

Oh hey, I didn't see you there.

Oh, hi.

[both laugh]

So yeah, so this is the living room.

We love movies.

[Seth] Yeah.

We love watching movies as a family.

We watch Mandalorian a lot on here for sure.

Our coffee table is made by Concrete Collaborative,

which is a group of sisters from Australia,

woman owned company based out of California,

and it's really, really, really beautiful

and carries on this theme of glamorous Cretaceous.

[Seth] We love this terrazzo element

and there's a few other places in the house,

like the breakfast area, that incorporates that

and it looks really cool.

So I directed a documentary called Dads

a couple of years ago, and when I did Dads,

I interviewed Jimmy Kimmel

and he told me a story about his oldest daughter,

that was Katie Kimmel, and she's made our lamps

and a few other pieces.

We have two Abyssinian cats that we're pretty obsessed with,

and this is one of them.

When we first came here,

this all looked like speaker system

and it is hiding speakers,

but instead of just having that classic black speaker look,

we shifted this out, added the brass,

put in this kind of beige color back here.

We brought in a lot of circular elements into the house

to kind of enhance that retro future vibe.

This is a pillow, it's a custom made pillow.

We have quite a number of these throughout the house.

They're really cozy.

They're great for the lumbar spine.

And Claire has called them pearl pillows,

so that is what they shall be called.

[light music]

So something about the kitchen in general

is that we actually kind of transformed the kitchen,

but without doing a lot of renovation work.

These are the original counters and cabinetry,

but we changed some key things in the kitchen

that allowed it to be completely transformed.

The color palette for the entire house

is pretty much pink and green.

That's really showcased here in the kitchen,

where it's just pink and green.

So the furniture is all Serena and Lily,

which is so durable and so easy and so chic

and I absolutely adore it.

Fire Clay Tile is a B corp,

which means that it's an employee owned company

and they're doing remarkable work.

And this tile in particular

is part of their desert collection,

and what they are committed to doing

in particular with the desert collection

is that they are giving a portion of their proceeds

to support the environment around the Sonoran desert.

It's beautiful tile and it's beautiful for the world,

and that's something that is wonderful.

[upbeat music]

We changed out a lot of the plumbing fixtures in the house,

and this one is by Signature Hardware

and we wanted to continue the brass story in the home,

so you see a lot of brass everywhere, which I love.

It's very nice.

Because Claire is so, so, so adept at cooking,

we sort of were like, Just outfit the kitchen, please.

Just tell us what we should have.

And so it's not just chic stuff,

there's, everything looks really nice,

but it's also very very practical.

So we've actually been cooking a lot more

now that we live in this home,

and it was also something

that we got a little bit better at during the pandemic.

That's for sure.

It's a work in progress.

Work in progress.

So this is the casual breakfast or dinner area.

So we have another fun table here by Concrete Collaborative,

those Australian sisters that we love so much.

My favorite thing is actually behind Bryce right here.

You might recognize this guy.

This is baby Yoda.

So I love baby Yoda.

A lot of people love baby Yoda,

but I really, really, really love baby Yoda

to the point where I'm sort of like, he's my son,

because I've had the tremendous privilege

of directing on the Mandalorian since season one,

and so Claire Thomas went to Katie Kimmel and said,

We would love to, in addition to having the cat,

we would love to also have a garlic holder

that is a baby Yoda.

It's pretty awesome.

It's the best. I don't wanna break it.

Yeah, don't.

[Bryce laughs]

[light music]

This is our guest bedroom, and we also use this bedroom

when we're on different schedules, which happens...

Happens a lot.

Happens enough of the time, yeah.

Oh, we added this Tambour wood to the wall,

just to add some texture, do something cool with it.

All of the furniture is from Anthropologie.

I love the shape of this because it's kind of like a smile.

It's really cute.

Just having soothing vibes, something that's relaxing,

especially if we're using it when we've been working

or overworked and need some time to ourselves.

It's just kind of something that feels

like you can recuperate and recover,

and then also have the Everhem shades

to just black out the room and sleep,

if you need to, during the daytime.

[light music]

I am in the guest bathroom right now

and it's more retro futuristic vibes in here.

This tile is by Lived In,

and one of the things that I love about it

is that it's made out of recyclable materials,

and it's completely the colors of our house.

So we just love the greens

and kind of the pinks, peachy tones.

Another sort of fun little detail,

this looks like the Mandalorian helmet.

So when I see this tile, I'm like,

Oh, Mando, which is fun.

[light music]

Welcome to the main bedroom in the house.

Don't say it.

This is where the magic happens.

[both laugh]

I've wanted to say that for our entire relationship.

Mm.

This has been a running joke.

Now that you've gotten it out of your system.

Now that I've gotten out of my system.

I just wanna say that this is where the magic happens.

She said it again.

Mm.

And all the furniture in here is from Lulu and Georgia,

and it's beautiful and it's so cozy

and I think this is my favorite room.

It's really soothing.

It calms you down, and it's really restful

and warm and just loving.

We actually, on the walls, have a custom lime wash

from Portella Paints.

There's also the light fixtures and the lamps

and all of that are quite whimsical and playful and fun.

And even with the furniture,

because we're inspired by that sort of 1980s retro futurism,

with a little bit of a Michelle Pfeiffer Scarface energy

to it as well.

It's a little sexy, it's a little sexy.

Yeah, that up there is sort of like a nest.

I just absolutely love it.

It's very soothing to fall asleep at night,

looking at that nest.

You sort of can get lost in it.

These lamps are really fun to play with.

I really like to just play with them and touch them,

and they're incredibly unique.

So here are just a few of our favorite

little vintage pieces,

but something that's new that we absolutely love.

My birthday present.

It was Seth's birthday present this year,

and this is an embroidered piece,

and the kids call us Mumsie and Whoopsie.

The kids call me Mumsie and they call him Whoopsie,

sometimes Whoops.

And it has cherry blossoms.

And it's again, it's the pink and green.

You can't get enough of the pink and green.

I love this sofa from Lulu and Georgia

because it's just really, really, really cozy,

and it has again, these pearl pillows that Claire made.

[light music]

I am in the main bedroom in our house,

and you'll notice on the walls

that there's wallpaper of dinosaurs.

This wallpaper was actually first presented to my daughter.

She has very sophisticated taste and she's a minimalist,

and she was sort of like,

That's cute, but A, I hate pink,

and B, that's a pretty loud print.

And I immediately jumped on it and I was like,

Claire, can I please have that?

Can I please have that in our bedroom?

I'm in the Jurassic World movies and those have dinosaurs,

and I'm very grateful to the dinosaurs in my life

that allowed for us to purchase this home.

A woman named Vivian Baker

has been my makeup artist for years.

She won an Oscar just a couple of years ago,

and she and her husband have a company

called the Makeup Light,

and it's something that they created

so that when you look in the mirror,

there's cinema grade lighting that will light you

so that you can actually see

what your face is gonna look like under the lights.

I have this little turn dial thing,

which can turn it up and you can turn it down.

And it's just, it's a beautiful, beautiful, beautiful space.

[light music]

So here we are in the main bathroom,

and while it's also my husband's bathroom,

he refers to it as Bryce's bathroom, which I appreciate.

Fire Clay Tile again,

and it's glazed brick and it's called Seguaro,

and one of the things that I love about this

that Claire pointed out to us early

is that it kind of looks like watercolor,

because there are irregularities from tile to tile

in a way that feels just really organic

and natural and beautiful.

We also have terrazzo through here, all custom terrazzo,

on the counter here.

So I absolutely adore the drapes that are in here.

They're also in the bedroom.

It's really peaceful.

It's really beautiful.

It's all the color tones that we love.

And we actually, from Signature Hardware, found a green tub,

which is so cute.

So there's a green tub here.

Of course, as well, There's a zillion trillion plants.

[light music]

Because the house, the exterior of the house was all white,

it was just an opportunity to paint something.

And so this is a mural of the twin suns from Tatooine,

which is a planet that Luke Skywalker is from

in Star Wars.

So all the outdoor furniture here is by Outer,

and what's really cool about it

is that the covers are built into it,

so you don't need to hide them or figure out where they are.

They're actually behind the cushions

and you just pull 'em over the top,

and everything's protected.

This piece here is by Our House,

and the plan is to just hang out

and spend some time by the fire.

[light music]

AD, thank you so much for coming. You are welcome anytime.

But right now, I'm gonna go get ready for a wrap party

for my latest directing project.

See you later.

[light music]
